"This is no game, Li’sar! Orcs have encamped across the river. This is elven "
"country; they are fools to enter here. We Elves are fast and hard to hit in "
"forests. You must defeat their leader so they never threaten us again. I "
"will advise you."
msgstr ""
"这不是游戏，莉莎！兽人已经在河对岸扎了营。这里是精灵的国度；胆敢入侵这里，他"
"们真是一群蠢货。我们精灵在森林中行动迅速而且难以击中。你必须击败他们的首领，"
"这样他们就再也不会来威胁我们了。我会向你提供建议的。"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:174
msgid "What should I do?"
msgstr "我该做什么？"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:175
msgid "female^What should I do?"
msgstr "我该做什么？"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:178
msgid ""
"First, we will have to deal with the Orcish Grunt stationed in the middle of "
"the river. He should be little trouble."
msgstr "首先，我们必须解决掉驻守在河中间的兽人步兵。他应该只是小菜一碟。"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:180
msgid ""
"By then, their leader will have recruited more units to send against us and "
"the real fight will begin."
msgstr ""
"那时，他们的首领肯定已经征募了更多单位来进攻我们，而真正的战斗就会打响。"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:182
msgid ""
"See this dark blue water? It’s too deep for either side to cross. The orcs "
"could slowly wade through that narrow band of shallow lighter-blue water in "
"the east; but we could stand on the shore and force them to fight us from "
"the water, where they are exposed and we are protected by the forest."
msgstr ""
"看到那些深蓝色的水域了吗？那些地方水太深，双方都无法通过。兽人们可以从东面狭"
"窄的浅蓝色水域中缓慢地渡河，不过我们可以坚守河岸，迫使他们站在水中和我们战"
"斗，那时他们将暴露在外，而我们则处在森林的保护之下。"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:184
msgid ""
"The more likely attack, then, is across the bridge. That middle island is "
"the key: it has a village for healing injured units and forests in which we "
"fight so well."
msgstr ""
"接着，他们就最有可能过桥来攻击我们了。中间的小岛是关键：那里有一座村庄可以治"
"疗受伤的单位，而岛上的森林会让我们如鱼得水。"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:188
msgid "Let’s go! Attack!"
msgstr "我们出发吧！进攻！"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#. The "us" in "let's" refers to Galdrad and Li'sar.
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:190
msgid "female^Let’s go! Attack!"
msgstr "我们出发吧！进攻！"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:195
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Hang on! You need to gather your forces. Or do you intend to fight the "
#| "orcs singlehandedly?"
msgid ""
"Hang on! You need to gather your forces. Or do you intend to fight the orcs "
"single-handedly?"
msgstr "等等！你得把自己的部队组织起来。还是说你想单枪匹马去和兽人战斗？"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:208
msgid ""
"I see you have veteran troops from your training! You should <i>recall</i> "
"them so as to start off the battle with more experienced units. Think "
"carefully, though; if a unit has too little experience, it might be better "
"to recruit a new one."
msgstr ""
"我发现你从训练里带来了老兵！你应该<b>召回</b>他们，这样就可以让更有经验的单位"
"来开启战局了。不过，一定要三思而行；如果一个单位的经验太少，那么征募一个新单"
"位反而更好。"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:214
msgid ""
"Some of your units have also managed to level up. They’re even more "
"formidable, so you should recall them as well."
msgstr "你的有些单位成功升级了。他们更加难对付，所以你也应该召回他们。"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:229
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, none of your troops survived your training, so you will have "
"to recruit new units. If you had any veteran troops, you could have "
"<i>recalled</i> them to battle this scenario. More experienced units would "
"have been of help against these orcs."
msgstr ""
"不幸的是，你的部队都没能在训练里活下来，所以你只能征募新单位了。如果你拥有老"
"兵的话，你本可以<b>召回</b>他们，让他们在此场景中战斗的。更有经验的单位本可以"
"在对付兽人时大有助益。"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:236
msgid "Recalling"
msgstr "召回"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:238
msgid ""
"In addition to recruiting new units each scenario, you can also <i>recall</"
"i> your experienced veterans from previous scenarios, for the cost of 20 "
"gold each. This allows you to build up a formidable army over the course of "
"multiple scenarios by recalling your highest leveled troops or those with "
"good combinations of traits and abilities. To recall a unit, right click "
"while your leader stands on a keep and select the <i>Recall</i> option. "
"Remember to also recruit new troops in addition to recalling old ones."
msgstr ""
"除了在每个场景中征募新单位以外，你也可以<b>召回</b>之前场景中的经验丰富的老"
"兵，每名老兵需花费20枚金币。这样，通过召回最高级的单位，或召回拥有优秀的特质"
"和技能组合的单位，你就能在攻略多个场景的过程中，建立起一支强大的军队。要召回"
"单位，当你的首领站在城堡主楼上时，请右击并选择<b>召回</b>选项。除了召回旧单位"
"外，也要记得征募新单位。"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:243
msgid ""
"You also have two new types of units to recruit this scenario: Elvish "
"Archers and Elvish Shamans. I’ll tell you more about them when you recruit "
"them. Personally, I would recommend a balanced force of two archers, two "
"fighters, and a shaman."
msgstr ""
"在此场景中，你也可以征募两种类型的新单位：精灵弓箭手和精灵萨满。当你征募他们"
"时，我会告诉你更多有关他们的内容。个人来说，我建议组织一支平衡的部队，有两名"
"弓箭手，两名战士，以及一名萨满。"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:246
msgid "Recruit or recall your troops"
msgstr "征募或召回你的部队"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:260
msgid "Elvish Shaman"
msgstr "精灵萨满"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:261
msgid ""
"The Shaman is a fairly weak unit, but she has the ability to <i>heal</i> "
"friendly units around her. She also has a special attack which <i>slows</i> "
"enemies, halving the damage they do for one turn."
msgstr ""
"萨满是一种相当脆弱的单位，不过她拥有<b>治疗</b>周围单位的能力。同时她也拥有可"
"以让敌人在一回合内<b>减速</b>的特殊攻击，这种攻击还会让敌人的伤害输出减半。"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:266
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:273
msgid "Abilities and Weapon Specials"
msgstr "能力与武器特攻"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:268
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Certain unit types have special <i>abilities</i>. Unlike traits, which "
#| "usually provide small buffs or debuffs, abilities give units special "
#| "behaviors that normal units do not have. In this case, the Elvish Shaman "
#| "has the Heal ability, which allows her to heal allied adjacent units 4 "
#| "hitpoints at the start of each turn. Unit types with abilities, "
#| "especially ones like Heal, can be very useful, so be careful when sending "
#| "them into battle.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Weapon specials are special attack modifiers that make certain attacks "
#| "more powerful. Once again, in this case, the Shaman has the Slows special "
#| "on her entangle attack. When this attack is used on an enemy, it will "
#| "halve the damage they do for one turn. Other weapon specials include "
#| "First Strike, which allows that attack to always hit first no matter who "
#| "attacks first, and Magical, which gives that attack a constant 70% chance "
#| "to hit.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "A full list of abilities and weapons specials, along with traits, may be "
#| "found in help."
